The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Hyderabad, Oct. 8: The Andhra Pradesh high court in an interim order allowed Suresh Gurumani, the sacked CEO of SKS Microfinance, to continue as director. Rejecting the plea by a shareholder to stay Gurumanis ousting as CEO, Justice Bhavani Prasad, however, refrained M.R. Rao, who succeeded Gurumani, from taking any new policy decisions without consulting the board.                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 8: The NSE and the BSE will start the 15-minute pre-open session call auction from October 18, NSE managing director and chief executive officer Ravi Narain said.                             
	 Calcutta, Oct. 8: There is likely to be a convergence on the proposed goods and services tax (GST) among the states at their next meeting, Asim Dasgupta, who is heading the state finance ministers panel on GST, said.                             
	 New Delhi, Oct. 8: The Supreme Court today asked the government to respond to the Comptroller and Auditor Generals report pointing out large-scale irregularities and favoritism by telecom minister A.Raja in the Rs 70,000-crore 2G spectrum allocation scam in 2008.                            
	 Dubai, Oct. 8: The UAEs Telecommunications Regulatory Authority has said the BlackBerry services in the country, which were due to be suspended on October 11, will continue as normal.                                                                                                                          
